    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "Most AI agent demos are fake productivity theater.\n\nCool for 30 seconds. Useless under real dev loops.\n\nSo I ran @StepFun_ai Step Plan through actual coding-agent workflows: Cline in VS Code + Claude Code setup, both using step-3.5-flash-2603.\n\nThis is where speed starts to https://t.co/UvQBVhR1Bc",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2063912600472285296",
    "time": "2026-06-08 17:14",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 08 09:14:44 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2063912600472285296",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "The dirty secret:\n\nAgents don’t fail because “agents are bad.”\n\nThey fail because every review, fix, retry, context check, and tool call becomes slow or expensive at volume.\n\nStep Plan is built for that boring layer devs ignore:\n\nfast, high-frequency model calls without duct",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2063912612925190233",
    "time": "2026-06-08 17:14",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 08 09:14:47 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2063912612925190233",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "In the first demo, Step Plan plugs into a VS Code agent workflow.\n\nThe agent reviews a frontend project, spots bugs/accessibility/security issues, explains the fixes, then keeps chaining work inside the repo.\n\nNot a toy prompt.\n\nA real loop: inspect → reason → patch → verify.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2063912625017389373",
    "time": "2026-06-08 17:14",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 08 09:14:50 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2063912625017389373",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "In the second demo, Claude Code gets wired to Step Plan and reviews a backend app.\n\nIt catches bad auth patterns, SQL injection risks, route issues, task validation problems, then applies fixes.\n\nThis is what agent infra should look like:\n\nless babysitting, more shipping. https://t.co/zM2hUiWsCR",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2063912704323236292",
    "time": "2026-06-08 17:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 08 09:15:09 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2063912704323236292",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "The point is not “another model card.”\n\nIt’s one plan that can sit inside the tools devs already use and make agents feel less like demos and more like infrastructure.\n\nCoding assistants.\nReview bots.\nInternal automations.\nAgent loops.\n\nThe wrapper era is getting squeezed.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2063912716432179711",
    "time": "2026-06-08 17:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 08 09:15:11 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2063912716432179711",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
